title: Javascript typeof fact
description: In JavaScript, the typeof operator returns 'object' for arrays, null, and even functions. This is because arrays and functions are technically objects in JavaScript.

title: Python timit fact
description: Python has a built-in timeit module that can be used to measure the execution time of small code snippets. This is useful for optimizing code and identifying performance bottlenecks in your Python programs.

title: React
description: React is a JavaScript library for building user interfaces. It uses a component-based approach where each component represents a piece of the UI and manages its own state and rendering. React components are written in JSX, a syntax that combines HTML-like tags with JavaScript expressions, and are compiled into JavaScript code that can be executed in the browser.
